ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was an interesting course which would be very helpful if you've never taken a class on signaling before. I would recommend it. I probably learned more in this course than any other graduate course at Yale.
I would highly recommend this class as I feel it is very important for any grad student in this program to obtain this type of knowledge
yes, i would recommend this course

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It helped with my qualifying exam preparation and is currently still helping me to sift through, read, and comprehend papers in my field and lectures of my colleagues. I think Signal Transduction is an important course for pharm students to take.
